parameters.description:
JSON serialized array of objects.
            Each object holds the information on column to be sort and corresponding sort type.
            The order in which objects are specified in array will be considered as sort priority i.e. First element holds the highest priority and so on.
            <code>        
            [
                {
                    "Name": "ColumnName1",
                    "SortType": "Ascending"
                },
                {
                    "Name": "ColumnName2",
                    "SortType": "Descending"
                },
                {
                    "Name": "ColumnName3",
                    "SortType": "Ascending"
                }
            ]
            </code>

Input: 
            {"GroupID_1":[],"GroupID_2":[SubGroupID2_1],"GroupID_3":[SubGroupID3_1, SubGroupID3_2,...,SubGroupID3_n]}
            <code>       
            1. Groups with all Subgroups: 
               {"100":[],"200":[]}
            2. Groups with a single subgroup: 
               {"100":[101],"200":[201]}
            3. Groups with multiple subgroups: 
               {"100":[101,102,103], "200":[201,202]}
            Combinations of 1,2 and 3 are also possible.
            </code>
